kidnapping call then, too?

137
00:09:23.207 --> 00:09:24.317
That's right.

138
00:09:24.837 --> 00:09:27.757
Manabu-san is all right, isn't he?

139
00:09:29.087 --> 00:09:32.717
Two hours have passed since the
ransom money was handed off.

140
00:09:33.517 --> 00:09:36.257
It's hard to be optimistic
given the circumstances.

141
00:09:36.257 --> 00:09:37.627
No...

142
00:09:38.307 --> 00:09:42.137
I'm having the police review the security
camera footage from the parking lot.

143
00:09:42.417 --> 00:09:47.647
The culprit who carried off the
ransom money should be visible.

144
00:09:49.117 --> 00:09:51.777
But we're already one step behind.

145
00:09:52.087 --> 00:09:56.957
Even if we find evidence that leads
us to the culprit, by that time...

146
00:09:57.617 --> 00:09:59.407
I did nothing wrong.

147
00:09:59.617 --> 00:10:01.657
Anyway, who are you?

148
00:10:02.537 --> 00:10:06.287
Me? I'm Mori Kogoro.

149
00:10:06.567 --> 00:10:08.807
Oh, I've heard of you.

150
00:10:08.807 --> 00:10:11.417
You're a famous detective from Tokyo.

151
00:10:11.417 --> 00:10:13.297
The something Kogoro.

152
00:10:13.297 --> 00:10:15.387
I believe it was...

153
00:10:15.847 --> 00:10:18.627
Yes, that's right. The Drunk Kogoro.

154
00:10:21.007 --> 00:10:23.097
Well, she's not wrong.

155
00:10:23.667 --> 00:10:26.637
You're wrong. It's the Sleeping Kogoro.

156
00:10:29.467 --> 00:10:30.437
Sir.

157
00:10:31.947 --> 00:10:34.737
Rintaro, where have you been?

158
00:10:35.147 --> 00:10:36.987
I'm sorry. I was busy.

159
00:10:37.157 --> 00:10:37.537
Hagino Rintaro (34)

160
00:10:37.537 --> 00:10:39.987
Is the master all right?
Hagino Rintaro (34)

161
00:10:40.197 --> 00:10:41.667
We don't know yet.

162
00:10:41.667 --> 00:10:42.867
Who is he?

163
00:10:42.867 --> 00:10:44.507
Manabu's apprentice.

164
00:10:44.507 --> 00:10:46.247
Apprentice of what?

165
00:10:46.557 --> 00:10:48.217
Printed silks.

166
00:10:48.217 --> 00:10:52.507
I see. Is the hostage a
printed silk maker as well?

167
00:10:52.717 --> 00:10:56.007
Yes. He used to be a famous
artisan around here.

168
00:10:56.447 --> 00:10:59.507
Used to be? Is he not anymore?

169
00:10:59.717 --> 00:11:00.617
No.

170
00:11:00.617 --> 00:11:03.337
Recently he had an accident
in the storage shed.

171
00:11:03.337 --> 00:11:05.517
He lost the use of his dominant hand.

172
00:11:14.137 --> 00:11:16.407
He was forced to give up his practice.

173
00:11:16.547 --> 00:11:18.657
That must be difficult.

174
00:11:19.267 --> 00:11:22.957
Right now his safety comes first.

175
00:11:22.957 --> 00:11:25.117
Is there anything we can do?

176
00:11:26.137 --> 00:11:30.167
Unfortunately, for now we can
only pray for his safety.

177
00:11:37.787 --> 00:11:39.557
It could be the culprit.

178
00:11:40.087 --> 00:11:41.557
Try to converse with them calmly.

179
00:11:45.217 --> 00:11:46.187
Hello?

180
00:11:46.647 --> 00:11:48.937
Sir, it's me.

181
00:11:48.937 --> 00:11:50.937
Manabu? Is that you, Manabu?

182
00:12:06.084 --> 00:12:07.174
I understand.

183
00:12:08.834 --> 00:12:11.584
After being released by the culprit,

184
00:12:11.584 --> 00:12:15.674
Manabu ran to a nearby police box
and was taken into their custody.

185
00:12:16.044 --> 00:12:18.514
Then Manabu-san is all right?

186
00:12:18.514 --> 00:12:20.554
Yes. He seems to be doing well.

187
00:12:21.184 --> 00:12:25.684
He'll return here after being
questioned by the police.

188
00:12:38.044 --> 00:12:39.204
Manabu-san!

189
00:12:41.114 --> 00:12:42.894
I'm glad you're all right.

190
00:12:42.894 --> 00:12:45.454
Master, I'm glad you're safe.

191
